    "extraction": {
      "analysis_type": "epistemic rupture",
      "analysis_type_plural": "epistemic ruptures",
      "core_question": "What revolutionary breaks created these concepts, and what had to be overcome for them to emerge?",
      "extraction_steps": [
        "IDENTIFY THE CONCEPTS: What key concepts are at play? When did they emerge? What's their current meaning?",
        "TRACE RUPTURES: Where are the discontinuities? What breaks mark 'before' and 'after'? Don't assume smooth evolution - look for revolutions",
        "FIND PREDECESSORS: What concepts came before? Same word, different meaning? Different word, similar function? What was right about them? What was wrong?",
        "IDENTIFY OBSTACLES (Bachelard): What epistemological obstacles blocked progress? First impressions? Verbal traps? Substantialist thinking? Prior scientific theories that became obstacles?",
        "MAP PARADIGMS (Kuhn): What paradigms are at play? What's their disciplinary matrix? What normal science puzzles do they define? What can't they see?",
        "IDENTIFY ANOMALIES: What doesn't fit the paradigm? How serious? How is it handled?",
        "TRACE PARADIGM SHIFTS: Where did one paradigm replace another? What was incommensurable? What was lost? What was gained?",
        "MAP RESISTANCE: Who resisted new ideas? Why? Was their resistance reasonable?",
        "RECONSTRUCT COGNITIVE LANDSCAPES: What could be thought in each era? What couldn't?",
        "BUILD CONCEPT LINEAGES: Trace how concepts evolved across periods - track semantic drift",
        "ANALYZE RESEARCH PROGRAMMES (Lakatos): What are the hard cores? Protective belts? Is the programme progressive or degenerating?"
      ],
      "key_fields": {
        "rupture_id": "The revolutionary breaks",
        "obstacle_id": "What blocked progress",
        "paradigm_id": "The frameworks within which science operates",
        "lineage_id": "The path of concepts across time"
      },
